data.content:
In .NET 10 (starting with .NET 9 SR1+), `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was removed because Android deprecated the resize mode. The replacement is the **keyboard accelerators / edge-to-edge** approach using `AndroidWindowSoftInputModeAdjust` combined with proper layout handling.

**Solution: Use `Resize` via the new Android edge-to-edge API**

1. In your `MauiProgram.cs`, opt back in to resize behavior:

```csharp
builder
    .UseMauiApp<App>()
    .ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>
    {
#if ANDROID
        events.AddAndroid(android => android
            .OnCreate((activity, _) =>
            {
                // Edge-to-edge is now default; ensure content resizes for keyboard
                AndroidX.Core.View.ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(
                    activity.Window.DecorView,
                    new WindowInsetsListener());
            }));
#endif
    });
```

2. Create the insets listener (in `Platforms/Android/`):

```csharp
#if ANDROID
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using AndroidX.Core.Graphics;

class WindowInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var systemBarInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.SystemBars());

        // Apply bottom padding so content moves above the keyboard
        view.SetPadding(
            systemBarInsets.Left,
            systemBarInsets.Top,
            systemBarInsets.Right,
            Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, systemBarInsets.Bottom));

        return insets;
    }
}
#endif
```

3. Keep your `AndroidManifest.xml` activity set to:

```xml
android:windowSoftInputMode="adjustResize"
```

**Why this works:** .NET 10 enables Android edge-to-edge by default. The OS no longer auto-resizes the window; instead you receive window insets and must apply padding yourself. The IME inset tells you the keyboard height.

**Simpler alternative** — if you don't need full edge-to-edge control, you can disable it in your activity's `OnCreate`:

```csharp
// Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs
protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);
    // Opt out of edge-to-edge to restore old resize behavior
    AndroidX.Activity.EdgeToEdge.Disable(this);
}
```

This restores the .NET 9 behavior where `adjustResize` works as before.
